title: Grateful Dead Live at Henry J. Kaiser Convention Center on 1987-03-01
description: Touch Of Gray-> Little Red Rooster, Peggy-O, Me & My Uncle, Mexicali Blues, When Push Comes To Shove, It's All Over Now, Row Jimmy-> Let It Grow Hell In A Bucket-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Samson & Delilah, Black Muddy River-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Space-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text:
hidden gem! This show is defenitly an overlooked show.  the first set is a well above mediocre set.  PEGGY O,
TOUCH,ROW JIMMY, LET IT GROW! BEAUTIFUL.
 The second set is defenitly out of sight. of course the scarlet-fire opener, which is always a great time. BLACK MUDDY RIVER In the middle of the set. that is what feeling and "in the moment" is all about. I also love the samson,He's gone, The other one, and the Black peter.  an all around great 1987 Grateful dead show for sure.  sound quality of show is just as good.  should be in everybody's collection.

                         peace.
